@* Views/Shared/_TermsAndConditions.cshtml *@
<div class="terms-conditions-modal">
    <h2>Terms and Conditions for Booking and Cancelling Appointments</h2>
    <h3>1. Booking Appointments</h3>
    <h4>1.1 Appointment Scheduling</h4>
    <p>
        Appointments can be scheduled online via our booking system, by phone, or in person at the salon.<br>
        To ensure availability, we recommend booking your appointment as early as possible.
    </p>
    <h4>1.2 Appointment Confirmation</h4>
    <p>
        Once an appointment is booked, you will receive a confirmation email or SMS. Please review the details to ensure accuracy.<br>
        If you do not receive a confirmation within 24 hours of booking, please contact us.
    </p>
    <h4>1.3 Personal Information</h4>
    <p>
        We require your name, contact information, and any specific service requests to process your booking.<br>
        All personal information will be handled in accordance with our Privacy Policy.
    </p>

    <h3>2. Cancellation Policy</h3>
    <h4>2.1 Cancellation Notice</h4>
    <p>
        To avoid a cancellation fee, we require at least 24 hours' notice if you wish to cancel or reschedule your appointment.<br>
        Cancellations made less than 24 hours before the scheduled appointment may incur a cancellation fee.
    </p>
    <h4>2.2 No-Show Policy</h4>
    <p>
        Failure to attend your appointment without prior notice is considered a "no-show."<br>
        Repeated no-shows may result in a non-refundable deposit requirement for future bookings or suspension of appointment privileges.
    </p>
    <h4>2.3 Cancellation Fees</h4>
    <p>
        A cancellation fee equivalent to [e.g., 50% of the scheduled service cost] will apply if you cancel within 24 hours of the appointment.<br>
        The fee will be charged to the payment method on file or deducted from any prepaid deposits.
    </p>
    <h4>2.4 Exceptions</h4>
    <p>We understand that emergencies can occur. If you need to cancel within 24 hours due to an emergency, please contact us as soon as possible to discuss possible exceptions.</p>

    <h3>3. Rescheduling Appointments</h3>
    <h4>3.1 Rescheduling Requests</h4>
    <p>
        Rescheduling can be done via our booking system, by phone, or in person.<br>
        Rescheduling is subject to availability, and any changes should be made at least 24 hours in advance.
    </p>
    <h4>3.2 Rescheduling Fees</h4>
    <p>If you reschedule within 24 hours of the appointment, a rescheduling fee may apply, similar to the cancellation fee.</p>

    <h3>4. Late Arrivals</h3>
    <h4>4.1 Grace Period</h4>
    <p>We offer a 10-minute grace period for late arrivals. If you arrive after this time, your appointment may need to be shortened or rescheduled.</p>
    <h4>4.2 Late Arrival Fees</h4>
    <p>A late arrival fee may apply if your delay impacts other appointments.</p>

    <h3>5. Salon Rights</h3>
    <h4>5.1 Refusal of Service</h4>
    <p>We reserve the right to refuse service to any client for inappropriate behavior, violation of salon policies, or if we deem it necessary for safety or ethical reasons.</p>
    <h4>5.2 Policy Changes</h4>
    <p>We may update these Terms and Conditions from time to time. Any changes will be posted on our website or communicated to you directly.</p>

    <h3>6. Contact Us</h3>
    <h4>6.1 Questions or Concerns</h4>
    <p>For any questions or concerns regarding our Terms and Conditions, please contact us at the contact numbers provided on our webpage per branch or our Facebook page.</p>

    <p>By booking an appointment with us, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to these Terms and Conditions.</p>
</div>
